definitions.definition: ( historical ) A former country in Southern Africa , in what is now Zimbabwe , originally called Southern Rhodesia, named after its founder, Cecil Rhodes. [used from 1964 to 1980]
( historical ) A historical region of Southern Africa , the area now occupied by Zimbabwe and Zambia . [used from 1895 to 1964]
